Reasoning: The paper presents a deep learning architecture for automated eddy detection and classification from Sea Surface Height (SSH) maps. This involves image processing and classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the study of oceanic eddies, which could potentially fall under the geophysics (cs.GR) sub-category.
